section.def:
applicant (申請人), in
            relation to an application made under section 29DJ(1), means the person who
            makes the application;

remaining co-buyer (餘下共同買家), in relation to an application made under section
            29DJ(1), means a co-buyer who, on the date of the application, remains a
            beneficial owner of the subject property concerned;

subparagraph.content:
was not a beneficial owner of any other residential property in Hong
                        Kong on the date of the applicant’s acquisition of the subject property;
                        and

was not a beneficial owner of any other residential property in Hong
                        Kong on the date of the co-buyers’ acquisition of the subject property;
                        and

original property A is transferred or divested from the applicant under
                        a conveyance on sale within the period specified in subsection
                        (7);

original property B is transferred or divested from the co-buyer under
                        a conveyance on sale within the period specified in subsection
                        (7);

if section 29DJ(1)(b)(i) is relied on in making the
                        application—the applicant became a Hong Kong permanent resident;
                        or

subsection.def:
acquisition mortgage (置業按揭), in relation to a subject property, means a
                charge by deed executed on the property for securing the repayment of a loan made
                for acquiring the property;

applicable instrument (適用文書) means an instrument—(a)under which a single residential property is acquired; and(b)on which, but for this Subdivision—(i)buyer’s stamp duty would have been payable; and(ii)stamp duty would have been payable according to Part 1
                            of Scale 1 of head 1(1), or Part 1 of Scale 1 of head 1(1A),
                            in the First Schedule;

buyer (買家), in
                relation to an applicable instrument, means a person who alone acquired the subject
                property under the instrument;

co-buyer (共同買家), in
                relation to an applicable instrument, means a person who, jointly with any other
                person, acquired the subject property under the instrument;

remaining specified scheme
                    co-buyer (餘下指明計劃共同買家) means a co-buyer—(a)who was, on the date of the co-buyers’ acquisition of the subject
                        property, covered by a specified scheme; and(b)who is a remaining co-buyer;

subparagraph.content:
